.TH simple_shell 1 "April 2025" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a minimal command-line interpreter written in C. It supports executing programs in your system's PATH and provides basic built-in commands.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.

.TP
.B env
Displays the current environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLES
Start the shell:
.B
./hsh

Run a command:
.B
ls -l

Use a full path:
.B
/bin/ls /tmp

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Abdulaziz Bin Jumaiah.

